value.0: The ascent narrows into a steep tunnel cutting through another stratum of earth. The air sinking down from higher altitudes is almost fresh in comparison to the conditions below. From above, there is an occasional cry or wail echoing throughout the pass.

Though the edges of the sinkhole appear a bit unstable, you manage to get close enough to see down into the ash-choked darkness below. You are fairly certain that this hole leads down to the Neesrepa Divide, and the natural chute that has formed looks safe enough to take down.

It would, however, be a one way trip.

A glimmer of diamonds...
